For range orders, if this is the first time the patient is receiving this medication for this pain rating, start with the lowest dose in the range. After one hour, if the patient reports ongoing pain that is unacceptable to the patient and the pain rating has not improved, give another dose of the medication such that the total dose does not exceed what is prescribed within that range. Reassess the patient one hour after this dose and if the pain rating is improved, the order is complete. If the pain rating is unacceptable to the patient and the pain rating has not improved, call the provider. If the patient has received this medication for this pain rating previously, start with the previous effective dose that is within the range prescribed.
